yeezus.cpu

Class CPU

  • java.lang.Object
    • yeezus.cpu.CPU
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable

    public class CPU
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Runnable
    This class emulates some of the CPU's actions in the yeezus Operating System. Once it has been assigned a PCB, it runs until the associated process has been terminated. The CPU fetches instructions from the MMU, decodes them, and executes them. Changes to the process data are reflected in the RAM.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Mark Zeagler

        Constructs a new CPU from the given parameters.
        Parameters:
        cpuid - The ID of the new CPU. NOTE: This must be a unique value.
        mmu - The MMU that manages this system's RAM.
        registerSize - The amount of registers to be used by this CPU.
        cacheSize - The size of the cache to be used by this CPU.
        Throws:
        DuplicateIDException - Thrown if the given CPU ID is not unique.

      • setProcess

        public void setProcess(@NotNull
                       PCB pcb)

        Sets a new process for this CPU.

        NOTE: It is imperative that Object.notify() be called on this CPU instance after using this method, or the thread it runs on will continue to sleep.

        Parameters:
        pcb - The PCB of the new process to be run by this CPU.

      • run

        public void run()
        Executes any process that is loaded into this CPU.

        NOTE: If there is no currently-set process, this method will cause its parent thread to sleep. To wake it up, use setProcess(PCB) to set a new process, followed by Object.notify() to begin its execution again.

        Specified by:
        run in interface java.lang.Runnable
        Throws:
        InvalidInstructionException - Thrown if the fetched Instruction could not be successfully decoded.
        InvalidWordException - Thrown if there was an issue with storing new data in the execution of the instruction.
        ExecutionException - Thrown if the CPU attempts to execute an I/O instruction (the DMA-Channel should handle that).
        InvalidAddressException - Thrown if an instruction tries to access an invalid address in memory.
        See Also:
        Thread.run()
